Fix pod sync with missing historical LFS

Allow automatic pod-to-host pushes to continue when Git LFS cannot
find old objects that were already absent from both the pod and host.

The workaround is limited to new destination refs. Git LFS sees those
as an all-zero old value and scans the whole branch, even when the new
pod ref is just another name for history already fetched from host/main
or another pod. For that case, upload only LFS payloads outside fetched
remote-tracking ancestors and skip the full-history pre-push scan for
the ref update. Existing ref updates keep the normal Git LFS pre-push
behavior.

Add regressions for a non-LFS pod commit on top of history with a
missing old LFS payload, and for a pod-created LFS pointer whose
payload is missing locally.
